## BOUNDED CONSTRAINT (NOT a wire bug ? intrinsic to gemma4_forward_cuda)
The -4 is gemma4_forward_cuda's own guard at cuda_forward.cu:1627-1629: in FULL mode (all-positions logits, which the daemon's prefill->chat needs) the TIED LM head reuses the resident f32 embedding, but a 12B-class OK_Q4B model keeps only packed codes in VRAM (g_w.embd==NULL) -> the full-vocab head is unavailable in the prefill forward and is reserved for the one-shot decode path (gemma4_decode_cuda, byte-untouched null floor). This is the SAME prefill-only / decode-not-hooked boundary the original WIRE-CUDA closure documented (sp_l1.h ?6). A full chat-decode of the 12B through the daemon needs a per-backend persistent-KV gemma4 decode hook (named follow-on: WIRE-CUDA-DECODE-GEMMA4), not a change to the bridge.
